LogFile.FinalText: Many households have a pet, and most people prefer a dog or a cat. So far, the fluffy pup is ahead of the dear kitten in the race of being the most popular pet in Denmark. While the dog's great loyalty explains its popularity, the many cat owners love their pet's independence. While the average cat owner finds a dog to be too dependent and filthy, many dog owners perceive cats as lazy and impersonal. Many pet owners chose a pet that reflects their own personality. When a big and strong man byus a big and strong dog, the dog's nature underlines the ego of its owner. Contrarily, feminine women often prefer a beautiful and elegant cat. Normally, dogs and cats get along without any problems, if they are used to one another. Often, the dog owner and the cat owner fight more than the dog and the cat.
